                Ebisu the Japanese god of fishermen and luck
              </div>
              <div class="articles__card__published-date">
                Published on 23 Feb 2022
              </div>

              <div class="articles__card__description">
                <i lang="ja">Ebisu</i>(<i lang="ja">えびす</i>), also
                transliterated <i lang="ja">Webisu</i> or called
                <i lang="ja">Hiruko</i> or
                <i lang="ja">Kotoshiro-nushi-no-kami</i>, is the Japanese god of
                fishermen and luck. He is one of the Seven Gods of Fortune, and
                the only one of the seven to originate purely from Japan without
                any Buddhist or Taoist influence. In Japanese mythology, the
                Seven Lucky Gods or Seven Gods of Fortune (<i lang="ja"
                  >七福神 - Shichi Fukujin</i
                >) are believed to grant good luck and are often represented in
                <i lang="ja">netsuke</i> (a miniature sculpture) and in
                artworks.
              </div>

