                Let's talk about tea. Tea is a common beverage for the
                Japanese—the Japanese loves a cup of hot tea to relax after a
                meal and often grabs one of many kinds of bottled tea at a
                convenience store or from a vending machine to keep hydrated
                throughout the day. For the Japanese, the quality of the hot tea
                served with the oshibori hot towel at a restaurant is indicative
                of the quality of the food to follow.
